Remarks made by Vice President Mike Pence during a visit to the National Hurricane Center in Miami, Florida. Pence thanked the staff for their expertise and highlighted the importance of remaining vigilant during hurricane season. He noted that while the projections for this year's hurricane season are better than last year, it only takes one hurricane to cause significant damage. Pence emphasized the administration's commitment to supporting state and local partners and improving disaster management. He also praised the advancements in technology and prediction capabilities at the National Hurricane Center. Pence briefly addressed questions about Iran and reiterated the administration's stance on preventing Iran from obtaining a nuclear weapon. He emphasized the United States' willingness to defend its forces and interests in the region but also expressed hope for a peaceful resolution.